    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To SortoutCode! ‚ù§Ô∏è Today I am going to show you How do you remove the hash(#) from the URL in the vue-router package in VueJS. Table of‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To SortoutCode! ‚ù§Ô∏è</p>\n<p>Today I am going to show you <strong><em>How do you remove the hash(#) from the URL in the vue-router package in VueJS.</em></strong></p>\n<p>Table of contains</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Setup the Vue (Optional)</li>\n<li>Setup the vue-router </li>\n<li>Remove hash(#) from URL from vue 2</li>\n<li>Remove hash(#) from URL from vue 3</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start today‚Äôs tutorial <strong><em>How do I remove the hash(#) from the URL in the vue-router package in VueJS?</em></strong></p>\n<h2>Setup the Vue (Optional)</h2>\n<p>First, we have to install the Vue project, I had installed the vueJS in my system. If you haven‚Äôt installed or have any problem with installation you can follow this article, it will show you step by step process of installation.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/blog/how-to-setup-vuejs-project/\" target=\"_BLANK\">How to Install the VueJS project?\n</a></p>\n<h2>Setup the vue-router</h2>\n<p>After the installation, of the vue project, Configure the <strong>vue-router</strong> module in your project. If you haven‚Äôt installed or have any problem with installation you can follow this article, it will show you step by step process of installation. It will also guide you, on how to show the router views using the <strong>router-view</strong> and how to use <strong>router-link</strong>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/blog/how-to-configure-or-install-vue-router-module-in-vuejs/\" target=\"_BLANK\">How to configure or Install vue-router module in VueJS?</a></p>\n<h2>Remove hash(#) from URL from vue 2</h2>\n<p>As you can see, The hash is in the URL <strong><em><a href=\"http://localhost:8080/#/\">http://localhost:8080/#/</a></em></strong> of the page. The hash is shown in every page link,</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/29114/hash-in-url.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.177215189873415%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Hash in URL\"\n        title=\"Hash in URL\"\n        src=\"/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/f058b/hash-in-url.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/c26ae/hash-in-url.png 158w,\n/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/6bdcf/hash-in-url.png 315w,\n/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/f058b/hash-in-url.png 630w,\n/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/40601/hash-in-url.png 945w,\n/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/78612/hash-in-url.png 1260w,\n/static/16c970cfc9272851f3f4c1526fd26bd7/29114/hash-in-url.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>To remove the <strong>Hash(#)</strong> from the URL, In vue 2 we have to use the <code class=\"language-text\">mode: 'history'</code> in the router as you can see in the example of VueJS 2:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Vue <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'vue'</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Router <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'vue-router'</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ComponentName <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'../components/ComponentName.vue'</span>\n\nVue<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">use</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>Router<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> router <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Router</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">routes</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"token literal-property property\">path</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'path'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"token literal-property property\">component</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> ComponentName<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"token literal-property property\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Your Component Name'</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">mode</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'history'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> router</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Remove hash(#) from URL from vue 3</h2>\n<p>We have created the two components that are <strong>FirstComponent.vue &#x26; SecondComponent.vue</strong></p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">FirstComponent.vue</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>template<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    This is First Component<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>template<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'FirstComponent'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">SecondComponent.vue</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>template<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    This is Second Component<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>template<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'SecondComponent'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In vue 3 we have import the <code class=\"language-text\">createWebHistory</code> then use the <code class=\"language-text\">history: createWebHistory()</code> code in your vue router module as you can see in the example of VueJS 3:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> createWebHistory<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> createRouter <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"vue-router\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> FirstComponent <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@/components/FirstComponent.vue\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> SecondComponent <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@/components/SecondComponent.vue\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> routes <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">path</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"/\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"First\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">component</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> FirstComponent<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">path</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"/second\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">name</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Second\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">component</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> SecondComponent<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> router <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">createRouter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">history</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">createWebHistory</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  routes<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> router<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>For now, let‚Äôs check the output for Vue 3.</p>\n<h2>Output</h2>\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sortoutcode/sortoutcode-images/main/removed-hash.gif\" alt=\"Remove hash from URL\" width=\"100%\">\n<p>All the best üëç.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to remove hash from URL in VueJS?","tags":["Vue"],"date":"July 13, 2022","description":"For example to remove the hash from the URL in the vue-router package step by step in vueJS - sortoutcode","social_image":""}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to install or configure vue-bootstrap in VueJS?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-install-vue-bootstrap-in-vuejs/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to configure or Install the vue-router module in VueJS?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-configure-or-install-vue-router-module-in-vuejs/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/how-to-remove-hash-from-url-in-vuejs/","prevSlug":"/blog/how-to-install-vue-bootstrap-in-vuejs/","nextSlug":"/blog/how-to-configure-or-install-vue-router-module-in-vuejs/"}},
